  "text": "These two approaches have been extended to systems. In [CITATION_1] Salo and Tzou followed the spirit of [CITATION_2] to prove uniqueness in the context of Dirac's equation. Isakov's argument was extended in [CITATION_3] to Maxwell's equations. The proof given here takes some ideas from [CITATION_4] and it turns out to be more convenient and useful for us than the proof given in [CITATION_5] . In fact, it avoids the long computations made there to prove the thesis of Theorem 2 and it allows to relax the hypothesis about the domain and the smoothness of the coefficients. In [CITATION_6] the domain was assumed to be of class C 1,1 and the coefficients were assumed to be C 4 . Besides, a technical hypothesis about the extension of the coefficients had to be supposed.",
